facts.fact_text: Austria's wholesale prices increased by 0.4% year-on-year in January 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: Wholesale prices in Austria increased by 0.4% year-on-year in January 2026

facts.fact_text: The wholesale price increase of 0.4% in January 2026 accelerated from a 0.1% gain in the previous month.

evidences.evidence_text: accelerating from a 0.1% gain in the previous month.

facts.fact_text: Significant price increases were seen for coffee, tea, cocoa and spices (+14.7%), watches and jewellery (+13.4%), as well as waste and scrap (+13.3%).

evidences.evidence_text: Significant price increases were seen for coffee, tea, cocoa and spices (+14.7%), watches and jewellery (+13.4%), as well as waste and scrap (+13.3%).

facts.fact_text: Wholesale prices fell sharply for other liquid and gaseous fuels and related products (-13.2%), grain, seeds and animal feeds (-13.1%), motor spirit (-9.0%), plastics and rubber in primary forms (-8.9%) as well as hides and leather (-5.0%).

evidences.evidence_text: On the other hand, wholesale prices fell sharply for other liquid and gaseous fuels and related products (-13.2%), grain, seeds and animal feeds (-13.1%), motor spirit (-9.0%), plastics and rubber in primary forms (-8.9%) as well as hides and leather (-5.0%).

facts.fact_text: On a monthly basis, wholesale prices rose by 0.7% in January, recovering from a 0.7% decline in the preceding period.
